# `seesaw-companion-ios` — Technical Architecture Blueprint
> **Purpose**: Authoritative technical blueprint for the `seesaw-companion-ios` iOS application. Designed for Swift 6+, iOS 26+, minimum viable scope for PoC. Uses MVVM + Clean Architecture with an AppCoordinator navigation layer. This document is the iOS counterpart to `seesaw-native` and must be read alongside the `seesaw-native` blueprint for the full picture.

***
## 0. System Role
`seesaw-companion-ios` is **Tier 2** in the SeeSaw three-tier architecture. It runs on an iPhone and acts as the intelligence bridge between the AiSee headset (Tier 1, BLE) and the cloud story agent (Tier 3, HTTPS).

```
AiSee Headset (seesaw-native)
        │  BLE GATT
        ▼
  iPhone (seesaw-companion-ios)   ◀── This app
        │  HTTPS/REST
        ▼
  Cloud Agent (seesaw-cloud-agent)
```

**What this app does in one interaction cycle:**
1. Receives scene input from the active wearable (JPEG over BLE from AiSee, or photo from iPhone camera)
2. Reassembles/captures the image and runs the on-device privacy pipeline (Vision + CoreML)
3. Builds a JSON payload of anonymous scene labels — no raw image, no faces, no voice biometrics
4. POSTs the JSON to the cloud agent and receives a story back
5. Converts the story to audio (AVSpeechSynthesizer) and sends it to the wearable output
6. Encodes audio as PCM, sends it back to the AiSee headset over BLE or plays via iPhone speaker

The app runs **silently in the background** for BLE mode. There is a parent-facing UI for status, camera preview, settings, and session timeline.

