## 3. App Navigation Flow

`AppCoordinator` is an `@Observable @MainActor` class that owns the root navigation state machine. It is bootstrapped in `AppRootView` as `@State` and drives the root `switch` in SwiftUI.

```swift
enum Route: Equatable {
    case launch      // LaunchScreenView — first-ever open
    case terms       // TermsView — EULA acceptance
    case signIn      // SignInView — Apple / Google auth
    case onboarding  // OnboardingView — 3-step wizard (accessory → child prefs → success)
    case home        // HomeView — 3-tab main screen
}
```

**Fast-path logic on subsequent launches:**
```
isSignedIn && onboarded  →  .home
isSignedIn               →  .onboarding
termsAccepted            →  .signIn
otherwise                →  .launch
```

**Coordinator actions:**
| Action | Next Route |
|--------|-----------|
| `getStarted()` | `.terms` |
| `termsAccepted()` | `.signIn` |
| `signInCompleted()` | `.onboarding` or `.home` |
| `onboardingCompleted()` | `.home` |
| `signOut()` | `.signIn` |

