## 7. Wearable Accessory Abstraction

The `WearableAccessory` protocol decouples `CompanionViewModel` from any specific hardware. All conformors expose identical `AsyncStream`-based I/O and lifecycle methods.

```swift
@MainActor
protocol WearableAccessory: AnyObject {
    var accessoryName: String { get }
    var wearableType: WearableType { get }
    var isConnected: Bool { get }

    var onConnected: (() -> Void)? { get set }
    var onDisconnected: (() -> Void)? { get set }

    var imageDataStream: AsyncStream<Data> { get }   // JPEG frames
    var statusStream: AsyncStream<String> { get }    // status strings
    var audioDataStream: AsyncStream<Data> { get }   // PCM from accessory mic

    func startDiscovery() async throws
    func stopDiscovery() async
    func disconnect() async

    func sendAudio(_ data: Data) async throws        // PCM → accessory output
    func sendCommand(_ command: String) async throws // BLEConstants.cmd* values
    func startAudioCapture() async throws
    func stopAudioCapture() async throws
}
```

### Wearable types
| `WearableType` | Conformor | Status |
|----------------|-----------|--------|
| `.iPhoneCamera` | `LocalDeviceAccessory` | Implemented |
| `.aiSeeBLE` | `BLEService` | Implemented |
| `.metaGlass` | `ExternalSDKAccessory` | Stub (SDK not integrated) |
| `.mfiCamera` | `ExternalSDKAccessory` | Stub (hardware not available) |

`AccessoryManager` persists the selection in `UserDefaults` and exposes `activeAccessory` via an exhaustive switch. Switching type takes effect on the next `startDiscovery()` call.

### `LocalDeviceAccessory`
Uses the iPhone's own hardware as a zero-external-hardware wearable:
- **Input**: `AVCaptureSession` (back camera, `.medium` preset, `AVCapturePhotoOutput`)
- **Mic**: `AudioCaptureService` tap via `AVAudioEngine`
- **Output**: `AVAudioEngine` + `AVAudioPlayerNode` (PCM Float32, 22050 Hz, mono)
- On `sendCommand("CAPTURE")`: fires `AVCapturePhotoOutput.capturePhoto` → JPEG yielded to `imageDataStream`
- On `sendAudio(data)`: schedules PCM `AVAudioPCMBuffer` on `playerNode`

