## 13. ViewModel (`CompanionViewModel.swift`)
Single `@MainActor @Observable` ViewModel for PoC. Owns three `Task` handles for stream observation that are cancelled on disconnect.

### Observable state exposed to SwiftUI
| Property | Type | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| `sessionState` | `SessionState` | Drives all UI control states |
| `lastError` | `String?` | Shown in error banner |
| `connectedDeviceName` | `String?` | Device name badge |
| `childAge` | `Int` | Used in `ScenePayload` |
| `timeline` | `[TimelineEntry]` | Session history (newest first) |
| `isShowingScenePreview` | `Bool` | Triggers full-screen debug overlay |
| `capturedImageData` | `Data?` | Face-blurred JPEG for preview |
| `sceneDetections` | `[DetectionResult]` | Bounding boxes for preview |
| `currentTranscript` | `String?` | Live / final PII-scrubbed transcript |
| `cameraPreviewSession` | `AVCaptureSession?` | Live camera (non-nil for `.iPhoneCamera` only) |

### Key methods
| Method | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `startScanning()` | Wires lifecycle callbacks, calls `accessory.startDiscovery()`, subscribes to image + status streams |
| `captureScene()` | Sends `BLEConstants.cmdCapture` to active accessory |
| `startRecording()` | Starts `AudioCaptureService` + live transcription stream |
| `stopRecording()` | Stops capture, calls `speechRecognitionService.stopTranscription()` |
| `runDetectionPreview(jpegData:)` | Calls `privacyPipeline.runDebugDetection` → sets preview state |
| `runFullPipeline(jpegData:)` | Full privacy → cloud → audio → send pipeline |

**Stream observation pattern**: `imageStreamTask` and `statusStreamTask` are `Task<Void, Never>` instances that loop over `AsyncStream` values from the active wearable. Streams are reset by the wearable on each `startDiscovery()` call; new tasks are created after `startDiscovery()` returns.

