## 20. Key Design Decisions
| Decision | Reason |
|----------|--------|
| `WearableAccessory` protocol | Decouples `CompanionViewModel` from hardware; enables iPhone-camera-only development without AiSee headset |
| `AppCoordinator` route state machine | Clean navigation without deep `NavigationLink` dependencies; enables auth fast-paths on subsequent launches |
| `AppDependencyContainer` | Centralises service construction; ViewModels receive injected dependencies; enables future testing |
| Firebase Auth (Apple + Google) | Parental identity required for child profile ownership; production-grade auth with zero custom server code |
| `actor` for all services | Swift 6 strict concurrency — eliminates data races without manual locking |
| `@Observable` ViewModels | iOS 17+ native observation, lighter than `ObservableObject` + `@Published` |
| `AsyncStream` for wearable I/O | Backpressure-safe; stream pair is recreated on each `startDiscovery()` to support reconnect cycles |
| Parallel vision stages (async let) | Object detection, scene classification, and speech recognition run concurrently — saves ~100–200 ms |
| `os_signpost` instrumentation | Every pipeline stage is measurable in Instruments without code changes |
| `PrivacyMetricsStore` + `PipelineResult` | Provides dissertation-grade audit evidence; `rawDataTransmitted: false` is a provable invariant |
| `PIIScrubber` as standalone enum | Single source of truth for redaction patterns; used by both pipeline and live transcription paths |
| PCM output (not AAC) for PoC | Removes codec complexity; AAC encoding is a future milestone |
| `LocalDeviceAccessory` | Enables full end-to-end testing without AiSee hardware; same `WearableAccessory` interface |
| `useTestImageForPreview` feature flag | Allows repeatable detection testing against a known asset without capturing a real scene |
| Zero `ChunkBuffer` in iPhone camera path | JPEG arrives in one shot from `AVCapturePhotoOutput`; no reassembly needed |
| 20 ms BLE audio write pacing | AiSee BLE buffer is small; pacing prevents `CBATTError.invalidHandle` drops |

